{
  "stem": "9899.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And my mother said, let us go-- she asked where the priest's house.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "She was hoping that a man of cloth, a religious man, would be able to help us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so each little town in Poland has a church, and next to the church lives the-- the parish priest.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he took us in immediately, asked who we were.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And my mother told him, we are-- she is the wife of a Polish officer who is fighting at the front.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And our house had been bombed-- she mentioned another city-- and everything was burned in it, and we had to leave.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we have no place to go, and won't he please help us?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "If he knew we were Jewish or not, we never found out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And in this little city, I don't if-- at that time, the pope, who is the pope today, lived.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And who knows?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Maybe it was him who helped us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In any event, we stayed at the priest's house for a week.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he fed us, and he gave us care.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was a very, very humane person-- didn't ask any questions.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then he told my mother that in order to settle in this town she needed to have papers.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the only way to get papers was to go to the gendarmerie, to the Germans, and they would interrogate her.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But she had nothing to fear, of course.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Being the wife of a Polish officer, they would give her the papers that would identify us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When those papers are given, it's very difficult to come by them because the Germans were suspicious.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Many Jews were escaping in that manner.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my mother left the baby and my oldest sister who looked Jewish with the baby.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
